edu.umn.biomedicus.numbers

Class EnglishNumeralsAcceptor

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.umn.biomedicus.numbers.EnglishNumeralsAcceptor

  • public class EnglishNumeralsAcceptor
extends Object
    Finds english numerals in text, like "one", "five eighths", or "three hundred billion and six". Will look for basic cardinal and ordinal numbers as well as fractions.

    It is not safe to use an instance of this class from multiple threads at once, use multiple instances for concurrency.

    Since:
    1.0.0

      • tryToken

        public boolean tryToken(String token,
                        int tokenBegin,
                        int tokenEnd)
        Sends the acceptor the token, which then checks it against the current state to try to detect numbers in an ongoing stream of tokens.
        Parameters:
        token - the token to test
        tokenBegin - the beginning index of the token
        tokenEnd - the end index of the token.
        Returns:
        true if with the token passed a number was recognized, false otherwise
